284 Anapalau Place
Honolulu, HI 96825
October 2, 1979
Mrs. Allyn Cole
390 C Haleloa Place
Honolulu, HI 96821
Dear Helen:
Enclosed is a draft of an article concerning your John
Rodgers cover.
With your approval I would like to sent it to
the Airpost Journal, the monthly publication of the American
Air Mail
But, first, I want your
thoughts.
I think I need the name
of your aunt who sent you - and the others in Honolulu - these
letters.
You will note the two blank spaces.
I am assuming that
she knew Rodgers, possible in Honolulu where he had been stationed
before his flight.
Also I am using your maiden name.
Any objections?
And
is it
correctly spelled?
As I read it from the cover it is
Hiserman.
I am suggesting that four other letters were sent by your
aunt to friends in Honolulu but I have not attempted to identify
the recipients.
I have written some of my aerophilatelic friends about
this
cover•
Some write that it is truly a
great cover; others don't
believe it.
One called it a hoax, but I think when he sees a
picture of it he will change his mind.
(He is,
by the way,
retired real admiral, and since it does not appear in the official
Navy record, it just can not be.)
Please let me have you comments - and your aunt's name.
Aloha,
cock
Jack Crampon
Telephone: 395-1769
